      <h3>1. what perch. is</h3>
      <p>perch. is a tool that extracts renewal details from emails, documents, and screenshots you choose to send us. we surface the provider, amount, renewal date, and a recommended action. we never act on your behalf, connect to your bank accounts, or access your financial data without you explicitly providing it.</p>

      <h3>2. eligibility</h3>
      <p>you must be at least 18 years old to use perch. you represent that you have the authority to agree to these terms on behalf of yourself or the entity you represent.</p>

      <h3>3. what you give us</h3>
      <p>you provide emails, documents, and data voluntarily. we store only what's necessary to track your renewals. you can delete any item at any time, and you can request full account deletion by emailing hello@perch.app.</p>

      <h3>4. what we do with your data</h3>
      <p>we extract renewal information from what you send us. we do not train AI models on your data. we do not share your data with third parties except as required to operate the service (e.g. email delivery, cloud storage). we do not sell your data. full details in our privacy policy.</p>

      <h3>5. what we don't do</h3>
      <p>perch. does not:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>connect to your bank accounts or payment cards</li>
        <li>cancel policies or subscriptions on your behalf</li>
        <li>negotiate with providers</li>
        <li>provide financial advice</li>
        <li>share your data with third parties for marketing</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>6. payment and billing</h3>
      <p>during early access, all features are free. when billing begins, we will provide at least 30 days' notice. starter tier is free forever (up to 5 renewals). standard tier is £8.99/month (£89/year). premium tier is £19.99/month (£199/year). all plans billed monthly unless you choose annual billing at a discounted rate. you can cancel at any time.</p>

      <h3>7. limitations</h3>
      <p>perch. is a tool for visibility. we make no guarantee that every renewal will be caught, every extraction will be accurate, or every verdict will be correct. you are ultimately responsible for your financial decisions.</p>

